                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/574: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Martin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-12T12:00:00-04:32"
                            >June 12, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Military attachés at Rio de Janeiro and Buenos Aires have telegraphed me that
                    they are proceeding to Corumbá and Formosa to receive Bolivian and Paraguayan
                    nationals held prisoners. At their request I have asked Bolivian Government for
                    advance lists of prisoners.</p>
                <p>Major Fleming has suggested June 20th as appropriate date for delivery of
                    Paraguayans at Formosa. I assume that the exchange should be simultaneous. If
                    the Commission expects to fix a date, please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Martin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
